data.name: Identify model
data.description: The Photo is a required parameter and is a base 64 encoded photo of the Subject for the facial recognition identify. The Confidence parameter is a value between 0 and 1.0 that indicates the confidence threshold at which a match will be included in the results. Count is the maximum number of matches that will be returned.

data.name: Identify Result
data.description: A list of key value pairs where the key is the matched SubjectID and the value is the confidence score of the match for that Subject.
